<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2246] Unset enum value is printed by ToString()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2246</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;if enum is not set, ToString() returns a first enum value, but it should indicate that field is empty&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;enum Distance&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
    DISTANCE_1      = 0,&lt;br/&gt;
    DISTANCE_2      = 1,&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;struct RaceDetails {&lt;br/&gt;
   1: optional Distance distance,&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c#:&lt;br/&gt;
new RaceDetails().ToString() &lt;br/&gt;
result: &quot;RaceDetails(Distance:DISTANCE_1)&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
expected: &quot;RaceDetails(Distance: )&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
